net.sf.jclec.mo.algorithm

Class MOECAlgorithm

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sf.jclec.algorithm.AbstractAlgorithm
      • net.sf.jclec.algorithm.PopulationAlgorithm
        • net.sf.jclec.mo.algorithm.MOECAlgorithm
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, net.sf.jclec.IAlgorithm, net.sf.jclec.IConfigure, net.sf.jclec.IPopulation, net.sf.jclec.ISystem, net.sf.jclec.JCLEC, IMOAlgorithm, net.sf.jclec.util.random.IRandGenFactory
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    MOEPAlgorithm, MOESAlgorithm, MOGeneticAlgorithm, MOGPAlgorithm

    public abstract class MOECAlgorithm
extends net.sf.jclec.algorithm.PopulationAlgorithm
implements IMOAlgorithm
    An abstract algorithm to solve multi-objective problems. It implements a general evolutionary process, where selection and replacement are delegated on an multi-objective strategy. The creation of offspring should be implemented by each specific evolutionary model (e.g. GA, EP, ES, GP).

    HISTORY:

    • (AR|JRR|SV, 1.0, March 2018) First release.

    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Aurora Ramirez (AR), Jose Raul Romero (JRR), Sebastian Ventura (SV)

    Knowledge Discovery and Intelligent Systems (KDIS) Research Group: http://www.uco.es/grupos/kdis

    See Also:
    PopulationAlgorithm, IMOAlgorithm, MOStrategy, Serialized Form
